\lim_{x \to 0} \frac{\tan x}{x}
= \lim_{x \to 0} \sec x\frac{\sin x}{x}
= \bigg(\lim_{x \to 0}\sec x\bigg) * \bigg(\lim_{x \to 0} \frac{\sin x}{x}\bigg)
= \bigg(\lim_{x \to 0}\cos x\bigg)^{-1} * 1 
= 1^{-1} * 1
= 1
